- main_bulb: Main Load (lamp) [inside enclosure: cube_load]
- internal_bulb: Internal Indicator Lamp [inside enclosure: cube_load] [NOTE: This lamp is connected in parallel with the main load and reflects voltage conditions across that branch.]
- load_diode: Load Protection Diode [inside enclosure: cube_load]
- load_cable_pos: Load Input Cable (+)
- load_cable_neg: Load Input Cable (−)

Instruction: Test for unintended feedback or ground loops from the load module back into the control module, by measuring the voltage at both load module input terminals and verifying their stability during lamp flicker relative to the power supply ground. Also, check if disconnecting the load module (while keeping the control and power module connected) eliminates the oscillation.
