description: Measure the voltage across the relay's switched output contacts (the wires feeding the load module) during a full oscillation cycle, to confirm if the relay is mechanically opening/closing, or if the output is experiencing voltage drops consistent with lamp flicker, and whether these correlate with control-side oscillations., outcome="Voltage at 'Control Output Cable (+)' is approximately 11.85 V, while voltage at 'Control Output Cable (−)' is approximately 0.02–0.03 V. The simulation did not converge, indicating an unstable or oscillating circuit state during measurement. No polarity inversion is detected in the measured cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Ambient Sensor Module (Power Supply Side),
description: Measure and monitor the supply voltage provided to the sensor and comparator circuit (not just the relay input), to determine if there are any fluctuations or noise present on the power rail that could cause circuit instability or oscillations. This will help identify if the issue is related to power supply stability or excessive current draw., outcome='The measured voltages indicate significant differences and point to unstable or oscillating circuit behavior, as simulation did not converge. The sensor shows 5.94 V at the positive terminal and 0.02 V at the negative, while the relay and resistor have voltages consistent with power presence but possible instability. No explicit polarity inversion is observed based on your measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Ambient Sensor Module (Light Sensor, Comparator, and PCB),
description: Visually inspect the light sensor, comparator IC, and PCB for any signs of physical defects (e.g., component damage, cold solder joints, corrosion, loose wires) or abnormal heat. This can help rule out hardware faults contributing to instability., outcome='The Ambient Light Sensor was visually inspected and no observable internal fault was found. No physical defects were identified during this inspection.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Ambient Sensor Module (Relay Component Itself),
description: Test the relay component itself for possible contact bounce or internal mechanical/electrical instability. This can be done by observing or measuring the voltage across the relay contacts with an oscilloscope, or replacing the relay with a known good one temporarily to see if mechanical bounce or intermittent relay failure is causing rapid oscillations., outcome='The Control Relay was visually inspected and showed no observable internal fault; it was in the closed state. Voltage measurements at the relay contacts were approximately 11.85 V (p) and 11.85 V (n), indicating a small voltage difference. The relay was replaced with a new unit, restoring parameters to nominal.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=155.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('replace_component', 120.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
